<TITLE> Ex-NBR director sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 14 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court has sent former NBR director Zahurul Haque and his wife, Afia, to jail on surrender in an illegal wealth related case. Metropolitan special judge Mozammel Hossain turned down their appeal for bail on Tuesday after the couple turned themselves in to the court at around 11:30am. The court earlier had sentenced Zahurul to 13 years in jail on twin charges of accumulating illegal wealth and suppressing the information to the Anticorruption Commission and his wife to three years in jail for abetting her husband. He was on the list of the top 50 corrupt politicians and other top professionals made by the graft watchdog during the 2007-2008 caretaker government
